<item>
            <title>[FELIX-2943] Component generated by @SlingServlet does not match default settings of @Component</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-2943</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using this annotation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@SlingServlet(
        paths = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;/my/cool/path&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;the auto-generated component shows up unexpectedly in the configMgr dropdown. Looking at the generated metatype.xml one can also see that the servlet is listed there as configurable.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the JavaDoc comment of @SlingServlets generateComponent() i had expected that a default (= empty) @Component annotation would be created, which of course has metatype = false as a default. This unfortunately does not seem to be the case, causing our configMgr dropdown to be flooded with config entries for all our (non-configurable) servlets.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Maven 3.0.2 / Felix Framework Bundle 3.0.2 / CQ 5.3 (No HF, no FP)</environment>
